BUS: Notes on newly expensive Proposal passage

Oerjan wrote:

>It would appear that my 2 Votes AGAINST the 3 Vote requirement only caused
>the supporters to cough up more support.  Fair enough.

>The reason I opposed it was that there would no longer be (and now there
>is not) any way to cheaply pass trivial fixes and public service Proposals
>that do not carry significant political interest.

Right.  It's time to make Disinterest meaningful again.

Proto: Real Disinterest

Amend R955 by replacing the text:

      If the Voting Index is greater than the Adoption Index for the
      Proposal, or if both equal Unanimity, and there were at
      least three votes in favor of the Proposal, then that Proposal
      is adopted.  Otherwise, it fails.

with:

      If the Voting Index is greater than the Adoption Index for the
      Proposal, or if both equal Unanimity, and either there were at
      least three votes in favor of the Proposal or the Proposal was
      Disinterested, then that Proposal is adopted.  Otherwise, it
      fails.

-- Crito


